  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Collaboration with Dairy Association of Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DAZ plays an instrumental role in the support of dairy cooperatives and through a partnership with Agriterra, DAZ is expected to strengthen its capacity to improve services provision to its members. Agriterra is seeing opportunities to directly support dairy cooperatives, but parallel to this, to channel support through DAZ to smaller and weaker cooperatives that are outside the Agriterra scope. Both strategies are expected to improve the position of dairy cooperative, in so doing boosting growth and development of the dairy sector in Zambia.

Short-term BHAG (2017): Increase milk productivity to 10 litre per cow per day, strengthen governance at member level through member capacity building and support to the research base to reduce cost of milk production by 15% per litre.                                                                                                                                                                    Long-term BHAG (2021): Increase milk productivity to 15 litre per cow per day, reduce cost of milk production by 30% per litre and become 60% financially sustainable.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Governance: At the member level, in particular small cooperatives, governance is considered weak. A governance ToT to DAZ staff aims to address this weakness. In addition, involvement of youth in the organisation and at member level will be sensitised.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Production: support to DAZ&apos;s research base is to inform the organisation&apos;s strategies on lobby &amp; advocacy and members&apos; capacity building.                                                                                                               Organisational Development: The newly-recruiting Cooperative Business Development Officer will be trained in Cooperative Development. 

Improving DAZ lobby capacity and capacities to strengthen cooperative membership for dairy development</narrative>
  </description>
